texts.text: For a guide about all the additions and changes in this update, see Bedrock Edition guides/Overworld Update.
The Overworld Update is the name for Minecraft: Pocket Edition version Alpha v0.14.0, a major update released on February 18, 2016.
The official name for the update, the Overworld Update, was revealed on February 18, 2016, the day of the release, in a blog post on the Xbox website.[1]

1 Notable features
1.1 Additions
1.2 Changes
2 Further revisions
3 References
Main article: Pocket Edition v0.14.0 alpha

Various additions to options.
10 new blocks:
Comparators, Dispensers, Droppers, Hoppers, Minecart with chest, Minecart with TNT, Minecart with hopper, Cauldrons, Red sandstone (alongside its variants), and Slime blocks.
3 new items:
Item frames, Maps, and Ender pearls.
Witch huts.
Witches.
Various changes to mobs, blocks, and items.

Alpha v0.14.1 added the Minecraft: Story Mode skin pack.
Alpha v0.14.2 fixed some bugs and crashes from Alpha v0.14.1.
Alpha v0.14.3 added the Biome Settlers Pack 2 skin pack.
